#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.114"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.114:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.114:0.2"
msgid "12. Kesivagga "
msgstr "12. With Kesi "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.114:0.3"
msgid "114. Nāgasutta "
msgstr "114. A Royal Elephant "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.114:1.1"
msgid "“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a royal bull elephant with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship. "

msgctxt "an4.114:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.114:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā ca hoti, hantā ca, khantā ca, gantā ca. "
msgstr "A royal bull elephant listens, destroys, endures, and goes fast. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.114:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a royal bull elephant listen? "

msgctxt "an4.114:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo yamenaṃ hatthidammasārathi kāraṇaṃ kāreti—"
msgstr "It’s when a royal bull elephant pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and lends an ear to whatever task the elephant trainer has it do, "

msgctxt "an4.114:2.3"
msgid "yadi vā katapubbaṃ yadi vā akatapubbaṃ—"
msgstr "whether or not it has done it before. "

#. VAR: aṭṭhiṃ katvā → aṭṭhikatvā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: sabbacetasā → sabbaṃ cetaso (sabbattha)
msgctxt "an4.114:2.4"
msgid "taṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto suṇāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.114:2.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo sotā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a royal bull elephant listens. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.117, sc3
msgctxt "an4.114:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo hantā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a royal bull elephant destroy? "

#. VAR: hanati → hanti (bj)
msgctxt "an4.114:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato hatthimpi hanati, hatthāruhampi hanati, assampi hanati, assāruhampi hanati, rathampi hanati, rathikampi hanati, pattikampi hanati. "
msgstr "It’s when a royal bull elephant in battle destroys elephants with their riders, horses with their riders, chariots and charioteers, and foot soldiers. "

msgctxt "an4.114:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo hantā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a royal bull elephant destroys. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.114:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khantā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a royal bull elephant endure? "

#. VAR: asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ → usuppahārānaṃ asippahārānaṃ (sī )
#. VAR: pharasuppah idaṃ padaṃ s1-3 potthakesu natthi
msgctxt "an4.114:4.2"
msgid "Idha bhikkhave, rañño nāgo saṅgāmagato khamo hoti sattippahārānaṃ asippahārānaṃ usuppahārānaṃ bheripaṇavasaṅkhatiṇavaninnādasaddānaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a royal bull elephant in battle endures being struck by spears, swords, arrows, and axes; it endures the thunder of the drums, kettledrums, horns, and cymbals. "

msgctxt "an4.114:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo khantā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a royal bull elephant endures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.114:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo gantā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a royal bull elephant go fast? "

msgctxt "an4.114:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo yamenaṃ hatthidammasārathi disaṃ peseti—"
msgstr "It’s when a royal bull elephant swiftly goes in whatever direction the elephant trainer sends it, "

msgctxt "an4.114:5.3"
msgid "yadi vā gatapubbaṃ yadi vā agatapubbaṃ—"
msgstr "whether or not it has been there before. "

#. VAR: khippameva → khippaññeva (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.114:5.4"
msgid "taṃ khippameva gantā hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.114:5.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, rañño nāgo gantā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a royal bull elephant goes fast. "

msgctxt "an4.114:5.6"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño nāgo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅganteva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "A royal bull elephant with four factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.114:6.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant with four factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an4.114:6.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.114:6.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā ca hoti, hantā ca, khantā ca, gantā ca. "
msgstr "A mendicant listens, destroys, endures, and goes fast. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.114:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant listen? "

msgctxt "an4.114:7.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye desiyamāne aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and lends an ear when the teaching and training proclaimed by a Realized One is being taught. "

msgctxt "an4.114:7.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sotā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant listens. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an4.114:8.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hantā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant destroy? "

msgctxt "an4.114:8.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti hanati byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … pe … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti hanati byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel thought. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, eliminate them, and obliterate them. "

msgctxt "an4.114:8.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu hantā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant destroys. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.118, sc9
msgctxt "an4.114:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khantā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant endure? "

msgctxt "an4.114:9.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya, ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant endures cold, heat, hunger, and thirst; the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; rude and unwelcome criticism; and they put up with physical pain—sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening. "

msgctxt "an4.114:9.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu khantā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant endures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an4.114:10.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gantā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant go fast? "

msgctxt "an4.114:10.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāyaṃ disā agatapubbā iminā dīghena addhunā yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ, taṃ khippaññeva gantā hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant swiftly goes in the direction they’ve never gone before in all this long time; that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment. "

msgctxt "an4.114:10.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gantā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant goes fast. "

msgctxt "an4.114:10.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these four factors … is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.114:10.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

